The paper deals with the problem of compressing and forwarding the baseband received signal and channel state information (CSI) from subsets of base stations (BSs) to central units (CUs) in network MIMO cellular systems. This involves the use of information theory and communication networks, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.IT and cs.NI. The paper also proposes various compression strategies and considers the use of distributed source coding, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI. Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of joint encoding and decoding in the uplink, which is related to the sub-categories cs.MM and cs.COM.
